WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:06.006
* Happy birthday, dear Maya

00:06.040 --> 00:07.541
Ooh, it's your birthday. You
won't fight me for the harmony.

00:07.575 --> 00:11.212
* Happy birthday to

00:11.245 --> 00:16.084
* You
* Yo-o-o-o-o-o-o-u

00:16.117 --> 00:18.186
Oh, thank you so much.
That was flat.

00:18.219 --> 00:20.020
So sweet of you.

00:20.054 --> 00:21.189
Here, open this.

00:21.222 --> 00:23.357
[ Giggling ] Ooh!

00:23.391 --> 00:25.859
Oh, a mug that says "Mom."

00:25.893 --> 00:28.028
An apron that says "Mom."

00:28.062 --> 00:31.399
And golf balls
that say "Mom."

00:31.432 --> 00:33.067
I don't golf.

00:33.101 --> 00:34.335
It's to add
to your collection

00:34.368 --> 00:36.270
'cause you collect
a lot of "Mom" stuff.

00:36.304 --> 00:37.571
You give me a lot
of "Mom" stuff.

00:37.605 --> 00:39.240
Yeah, and you're welcome.

00:39.273 --> 00:41.242
This one's from JJ.

00:41.275 --> 00:42.876
Okay.

00:42.910 --> 00:45.579
Slippers that say "Mom."

00:45.613 --> 00:47.881
"Not just any slippers.

00:47.915 --> 00:49.950
The bottoms are mops.

00:49.983 --> 00:51.285
Try them on."

00:53.321 --> 00:56.124
Okay.

00:56.157 --> 00:59.026
Oh, wow. It's just like walking,
but work.

00:59.059 --> 01:01.129
Oh, what is
the matter with you?

01:01.162 --> 01:02.096
[ Whispering ]
What is all this crap?

01:02.130 --> 01:03.431
It's her birthday.

01:03.464 --> 01:05.133
You're supposed to get her
something personal,

01:05.166 --> 01:06.434
something that says
you know her.

01:06.467 --> 01:07.935
Is any of this useable?

01:07.968 --> 01:09.036
Mine!
Does it say "Mom" on it?

01:09.069 --> 01:10.271
Nope, and it's nice.

01:10.304 --> 01:11.272
She said she wanted it.

01:11.305 --> 01:13.241
It's not the exact color
I wanted --

01:13.274 --> 01:14.542
So it's something to wear?
Absolutely.

01:14.575 --> 01:15.943
She'll love it.

01:15.976 --> 01:17.278
Dylan's gift is
from everybody.

01:17.311 --> 01:18.912
Well, they're wonderful.

01:18.946 --> 01:20.448
Look.
Already absolutely filthy.

01:20.481 --> 01:22.216
Hon, don't you get
the joke?

01:22.250 --> 01:23.584
These are all gag gifts.

01:23.617 --> 01:24.918
Guys, she fell for it.

01:24.952 --> 01:26.120
[ Laughter ]
[ Relieved sigh ]

01:26.154 --> 01:27.455
Only mom gifts.
How rich.

01:27.488 --> 01:29.123
Dylan, give her
the real one.

01:29.157 --> 01:31.091
Honey, this is what
you're all about.

01:31.125 --> 01:33.994
Thank you -- Oh.

01:34.027 --> 01:35.863
[ Box lid thuds ]

01:37.298 --> 01:38.532
Bags for picking up
after Pepper.

01:40.100 --> 01:41.169
And they're scented.

01:43.103 --> 01:45.273
Hey, I missed a spot
back there.

01:46.340 --> 01:47.508
[ Exhales ]

01:47.541 --> 01:50.478
Forget nice, expensive.

01:50.511 --> 01:52.513
You can wear it?

01:52.546 --> 01:53.947
[ Bag rustles ]

01:53.981 --> 01:56.350
Okay, it's a little tight.

01:57.451 --> 02:00.421
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:00.454 --> 02:02.256
**

02:02.290 --> 02:03.624
Maya: You know, I love
being your mom.

02:03.657 --> 02:05.426
I love taking care of you.

02:05.459 --> 02:07.094
I just don't understand
why you don't see

02:07.127 --> 02:08.128
the other sides of me --

02:08.162 --> 02:09.497
Darling, Ray likes
the blue plate.

02:09.530 --> 02:11.098
I'm a person.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.000
I have passions...
Ray, let go.

02:13.033 --> 02:14.335
...and interests and dreams.
I'm taking the plates now.
I'm not letting go.

02:14.368 --> 02:16.970
Ray, stop!
How can you think --
Separate! --

02:17.004 --> 02:20.841
I exist to serve you
and pick up af--

02:20.874 --> 02:23.377
Oh, Pepper.

02:24.878 --> 02:27.147
It is what I am.
This is me.

02:27.181 --> 02:28.982
You're not dog poop,
Mrs. DiMeo.

02:29.016 --> 02:32.019
I don't mean that
that's what I am.

02:32.052 --> 02:33.621
I mean the action
of cleaning up.
Let go!

02:33.654 --> 02:34.622
Ray: Mom, make her stop!

02:34.655 --> 02:35.623
Wimp.

02:35.656 --> 02:37.157
Of course that's how
they see me.

02:37.191 --> 02:38.359
It's all I show them.

02:38.392 --> 02:39.627
Joyce: It happens.
Not too long ago,

02:39.660 --> 02:41.195
I was in a toxic relationship

02:41.229 --> 02:43.163
with someone
I do not want to name.

02:43.197 --> 02:44.465
Kenneth.
And he only saw me

02:44.498 --> 02:47.034
as one thing -- a reliable
4:00 a.m. booty call.

02:47.067 --> 02:49.036
He comes here at 6:00.

02:49.069 --> 02:50.971
And I needed to show him
and myself

02:51.004 --> 02:52.406
that there was more to me.

02:52.440 --> 02:54.475
That's when I found
community theater.

02:54.508 --> 02:57.044
[ Gasps ]
"My arm doesn't
go that way."

02:57.077 --> 02:58.879
Hmm? Oh, him.
[ Laughing ] Whoopsie-do.

02:58.912 --> 03:00.581
I love theater.

03:00.614 --> 03:03.050
I did tons of plays in college.
What kind of plays do you do?

03:03.083 --> 03:05.018
Well, our troupe has some
trouble securing rights,

03:05.052 --> 03:07.888
so we do legally deniable
versions of the classics --

03:07.921 --> 03:10.057
"Sinking in the Rain,"
"Gals and Dudes."

03:10.090 --> 03:12.393
Oh, I played a carton of
half and half in "Creamgirls."

03:12.426 --> 03:14.928
Auditions are next week.
Would you like to come?

03:14.962 --> 03:16.530
Does this answer
your question?

03:16.564 --> 03:19.933
* What's that, people?
Is it true? *

03:19.967 --> 03:23.170
* That I am coming home
to the stage *

03:23.203 --> 03:25.339
Random.

03:25.373 --> 03:26.340
Would you like to come?

03:26.374 --> 03:27.841
Yeah.

03:27.875 --> 03:29.577
Hey, found Dylan's phone
in my car.

03:29.610 --> 03:31.912
Catch.

03:31.945 --> 03:32.913
Hey, Tom Brady.

03:32.946 --> 03:34.081
What'd you do with my dad?

03:34.114 --> 03:35.349
That feels surprisingly nice.

03:35.383 --> 03:36.517
Oh, snap.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.218
Huge party at Anthony Lopez's
house tomorrow.

03:38.252 --> 03:39.420
Is that what those
pictures mean?

03:39.453 --> 03:40.854
Yeah, it's a code.

03:40.888 --> 03:42.256
"Come at 9:00.
Bring drinks.

03:42.290 --> 03:43.257
No losers."

03:43.291 --> 03:44.558
I tutor this guy.

03:44.592 --> 03:45.959
Why wouldn't he invite me?

03:45.993 --> 03:47.895
I love parties
with no losers.

03:47.928 --> 03:48.962
They're just so hard
to come by.

03:48.996 --> 03:51.131
Kenneth:
Everyone, announcement!

03:52.600 --> 03:55.102
Oh, great, Kenneth.
I'd love to discuss you

03:55.135 --> 03:56.970
coming into work
a little bit later.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.406
Big news, guys.

03:58.439 --> 03:59.473
JJ?

04:01.975 --> 04:02.943
Hey.

04:02.976 --> 04:04.445
JJ got a vest.
No.

04:04.478 --> 04:06.046
Pretty sure that's a vest,
Kenneth.
Not the point.

04:06.079 --> 04:07.948
It's a vest
from my supermarket

04:07.981 --> 04:10.918
because he got a job there!

04:10.951 --> 04:12.252
[ Laughs ]
Bro.

04:12.286 --> 04:13.954
That's wonderful.

04:13.987 --> 04:15.456
We didn't know you were
looking for a job.

04:15.489 --> 04:18.225
He said he's ready,
so he applied to 20 places,

04:18.258 --> 04:20.127
got very nice rejections
from all of them,

04:20.160 --> 04:22.129
then I just got him a job
where I work.

04:22.162 --> 04:24.097
Starts tomorrow.
What will you be doing?

04:24.131 --> 04:26.900
"Kenneth has
something planned."

04:26.934 --> 04:28.502
Uh, yeah.
We'll figure it out.

04:28.536 --> 04:29.537
You haven't thought about it?

04:31.204 --> 04:34.274
"Wait. Is this a real job

04:34.308 --> 04:38.245
or a favor for a kid
with a disability?"

04:38.278 --> 04:41.482
I-It's the one
you want it to be.

04:41.515 --> 04:43.917
I mean, you of all people --

04:43.951 --> 04:45.519
you wouldn't just
give JJ a job

04:45.553 --> 04:47.888
to give him a job, right?

04:49.390 --> 04:51.291
No, that would be weird

04:51.325 --> 04:53.961
considering everything
we've been through.

04:53.994 --> 04:56.530
Look, we're forgetting
what matters here.

04:56.564 --> 04:58.165
JJ got a vest!

05:00.067 --> 05:02.302
That's Em. She's got a bit
of stage fright.

05:02.336 --> 05:04.037
She's kind of always mumbling
when you have to

05:04.071 --> 05:05.305
[Raises voice]
project like this!

05:05.339 --> 05:07.975
Yeah, 'cause those are
your only two choices.

05:08.008 --> 05:10.177
That's Colin. He is so good
at death scenes.

05:10.210 --> 05:12.179
He finds a way to die
several times per play.

05:12.212 --> 05:13.180
Everyone's great.

05:13.213 --> 05:14.382
[ Laughs ]
[ Door opens ]

05:14.415 --> 05:16.283
Ugh, except for him.

05:16.316 --> 05:18.952
He is the most difficult,
undirectable diva

05:18.986 --> 05:20.888
that you will ever meet.

05:20.921 --> 05:21.855
Hello, Richard.
Maya.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.023
What are you doing here?

05:23.056 --> 05:25.125
You don't know her,
jackass!

05:25.158 --> 05:28.128
Oh, save it for the loudness
contest on the stage!

05:28.161 --> 05:30.831
Welcome, everyone,
to this year's production

05:30.864 --> 05:33.401
of "142nd Street."

05:33.434 --> 05:34.868
Gosh, that is very close
to the real thing.

05:36.103 --> 05:37.538
Hey, Dad.
You wanted to talk?

05:37.571 --> 05:39.006
Yeah, you remember Dane.

05:39.039 --> 05:41.141
He's a dad at your school
and a friend.

05:41.174 --> 05:42.843
Yeah, and the seafood king
of Newport,

05:42.876 --> 05:44.311
but sure, dad and friend.

05:44.344 --> 05:45.579
That's my hook.
How could I forget?

05:45.613 --> 05:47.214
The halibut at DiSanti's?

05:47.247 --> 05:48.215
That's Dane's halibut.

05:48.248 --> 05:50.150
You've never taken us
to DiSanti's.

05:50.183 --> 05:51.318
You say it's overpriced.

05:51.351 --> 05:52.319
Liar.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.421
Ray, I'm gonna cut
to the chase.

05:53.454 --> 05:54.855
Do you know my daughter,
Sammy?

05:54.888 --> 05:56.189
Oh, yeah.
She's super popular.

05:56.223 --> 05:57.558
Yeah, well, she looks like
a female me.

05:57.591 --> 05:59.192
It's high-school-boy catnip.

05:59.226 --> 06:00.561
Sammy was going to go to
that secret party

06:00.594 --> 06:03.063
you told your dad about,
but he told me about that party,

06:03.096 --> 06:05.365
and I got it cancelled.

06:05.399 --> 06:08.201
Ray, you've done parents
a great service.

06:08.235 --> 06:10.070
We could use the help

06:10.103 --> 06:14.074
of a smart young man like you
on an ongoing basis.

06:14.107 --> 06:15.075
Would that interest you
at all?

06:15.108 --> 06:16.209
Look, I know my fellow teens

06:16.243 --> 06:18.045
don't appreciate me,
but I am no rat.

06:18.078 --> 06:19.379
Who'd call you a rat?

06:19.413 --> 06:20.581
Boy, you're amazing.

06:20.614 --> 06:22.450
You're smart,
you're interesting.

06:22.483 --> 06:23.784
I'll tell you everything.

06:23.817 --> 06:25.519
[ Piano plays ]

06:25.553 --> 06:27.020
* Famous street

06:27.054 --> 06:29.590
* Where the stars all meet

06:29.623 --> 06:31.258
* And a hundred streets

06:31.291 --> 06:32.292
* Away from that street

06:32.325 --> 06:33.894
* 142nd

06:33.927 --> 06:36.363
[ Quietly ] * Street

06:36.396 --> 06:37.931
Joyce:
* On the subway, 1, 2, 3

06:37.965 --> 06:39.266
* Change at 96th Street

06:39.299 --> 06:42.069
* Would be my suggestion

06:42.936 --> 06:44.304
Maya: * If you'd rather go
above ground *

06:44.337 --> 06:45.906
* Take the M-1 bus downtown

06:45.939 --> 06:48.275
* And walking's not
out of the question *

06:48.308 --> 06:50.811
This is fantastic!

06:50.844 --> 06:52.546
Alright, JJ.

06:52.580 --> 06:56.984
Here is your name tag
and 300-page store manual.

06:58.519 --> 07:01.254
That nobody reads.
Alright. Let's do this.

07:01.288 --> 07:04.291
"What am I doing?"

07:04.324 --> 07:06.259
Well, self-checkout
is always breaking,

07:06.293 --> 07:08.462
error codes up the wazoo.

07:08.496 --> 07:10.631
You can stand in front
and direct folks

07:10.664 --> 07:13.133
to the regular
checkout line.

07:13.166 --> 07:16.303
"And is this a real job?"

07:16.336 --> 07:19.072
Of course. Quincy was doing it
before you.

07:19.106 --> 07:20.808
Let's see you do it.

07:20.841 --> 07:22.075
Oh, excuse me, Miss.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.512
May I recommend
the self-checkout?

07:24.545 --> 07:26.279
Oh, yes. Thank you.

07:31.351 --> 07:32.953
It's broken. Go that way.

07:35.022 --> 07:35.923
Why would you
do that to me?

07:35.956 --> 07:39.426
**

07:39.459 --> 07:40.961
Oh, thanks
for coming with me.

07:40.994 --> 07:42.329
This is a big moment
for Mommy.

07:42.362 --> 07:44.331
Dylan: I'm sorry we got you
such lousy presents,

07:44.364 --> 07:46.366
but it seems like it led
to something good.

07:46.399 --> 07:48.035
Something great.

07:48.068 --> 07:50.037
Now I get to share my talent
with the world and my kids.

07:50.070 --> 07:52.039
You know what?
I'm gonna get you a new mug,

07:52.072 --> 07:53.206
whatever part you get.

07:53.240 --> 07:55.843
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:55.876 --> 07:58.278
"Play cancelled due to
lack of talent"?

07:58.311 --> 08:00.514
I'm not the best
with gifts,

08:00.548 --> 08:02.215
but you don't want that
on a mug, right?

08:06.554 --> 08:07.988
So do we just
ask him stuff?

08:08.021 --> 08:09.156
Ask him anything you want.
He's here to please.

08:09.189 --> 08:12.059
But how do we know that
he's really plugged in

08:12.092 --> 08:13.160
to what the teens
are doing?

08:13.193 --> 08:15.028
Show 'em, Ray.

08:15.062 --> 08:17.497
[ Electronic dance music
plays ]

08:17.531 --> 08:24.538
**

08:24.905 --> 08:26.373
[ Record scratch ]

08:26.406 --> 08:27.641
Any questions?

08:27.675 --> 08:29.543
Ray, my son, Lyndon,
says he's single,

08:29.577 --> 08:31.378
but I don't believe him.

08:31.411 --> 08:33.881
Do you know?
Lyndon's dating Vanessa Diaz.

08:33.914 --> 08:36.049
I know that because I
accidentally looked at her once,

08:36.083 --> 08:38.218
and he tried to
push me down the stairs.

08:38.251 --> 08:40.387
Ray, did my daughter, Nell,
quit cross country?

08:40.420 --> 08:41.589
Oh, yeah.

08:41.622 --> 08:43.056
She smokes every day
after school.

08:43.090 --> 08:44.658
I warned her about emphysema,

08:44.692 --> 08:46.226
but she tried to push me
down the stairs.

08:46.259 --> 08:48.361
Do you know of any
big parties coming up?

08:48.395 --> 08:50.097
Jocks like to keep
their parties secret,

08:50.130 --> 08:52.499
but a secret ain't nothing
but a piece of cheese,

08:52.532 --> 08:53.601
and a rat's got to eat.

08:53.634 --> 08:55.402
[ Parents murmuring ]

08:55.435 --> 08:56.536
The play's cancelled?

08:56.570 --> 08:57.905
What a shame.

08:57.938 --> 08:59.539
You know, I just bought
this really skanky dress

08:59.573 --> 09:01.241
to wear to the wrap party.

09:01.274 --> 09:03.010
Wait, that's it?
You're just going to give up?

09:03.043 --> 09:05.245
No, h play's cancelled.
Let's do our own play.

09:05.278 --> 09:07.247
Really?
You mean we'll put it on?
Yeah.

09:07.280 --> 09:10.083
Stage it and make costumes?
Yes.

09:10.117 --> 09:12.085
And we'll use the coming-of-age
musical I wrote about my life?

09:13.120 --> 09:14.354
Um, maybe.

09:14.387 --> 09:17.190
We'll show that director
and everyone else

09:17.224 --> 09:19.192
that there is more to us
than they think.

09:19.226 --> 09:21.094
Yeah, I'm with Maya.

09:21.128 --> 09:22.395
Come on, everybody
but Richard.

09:22.429 --> 09:23.363
Let's do it.

09:23.396 --> 09:24.364
Whoo-hoo!

09:24.397 --> 09:31.404
**

09:32.105 --> 09:39.112
**

09:40.413 --> 09:43.283
[ Beeping ]

09:43.316 --> 09:46.386
Oh, I see you've...

09:46.419 --> 09:48.421
met Quincy.

09:48.455 --> 09:54.127
"You gave me the job
of a piece of cardboard."

09:54.161 --> 09:55.996
No, I gave you a job
that needs to be done,

09:56.029 --> 09:58.465
and now that you know
about Quincy,

09:58.498 --> 09:59.967
he can get back to work.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.068
Hey, Quincy.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.602
You're back
on cheese samples.

10:02.636 --> 10:04.471
Any problem with that?
No?

10:04.504 --> 10:07.007
Team player.

10:09.309 --> 10:11.144
[ Indistinct talking ]

10:11.178 --> 10:13.146
I think we really need
to assign parts.

10:13.180 --> 10:14.314
Oh, oh, I want
to be the doctor.

10:14.347 --> 10:15.482
You, a doctor?

10:15.515 --> 10:17.584
-I want to be the doctor.
-Two doctors.

10:17.617 --> 10:19.419
There's no doctor
in the play.

10:19.452 --> 10:21.254
Oh.
We really need order.

10:21.288 --> 10:23.356
You know, what we need
is a director.

10:23.390 --> 10:25.192
-I nominate Maya.
-Ooh.

10:25.225 --> 10:26.359
-Maya!
-Yes, Maya!

10:26.393 --> 10:28.161
Actor-director?

10:28.195 --> 10:29.629
We have so much to do.

10:29.663 --> 10:31.131
There's no time
for false modesty.

10:31.164 --> 10:33.133
Bow down
before your hyphenate.

10:33.166 --> 10:35.102
Yo, party tomorrow
at Zayden's.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.336
Send out the text.

10:36.369 --> 10:38.071
The last one got cancelled,
so keep it quiet.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.308
Excuse me for a minute.

10:41.341 --> 10:43.877
I seem to have come down
with a touch of diarrhea.

10:43.911 --> 10:46.313
[ Harry Nilsson's
"Jump into the Fire" plays ]

10:46.346 --> 10:49.616
**

10:49.649 --> 10:50.851
[ Cellphone chimes ]

10:50.884 --> 10:52.119
Are you kidding me?

10:52.152 --> 10:53.286
It's cancelled.

10:53.320 --> 10:56.023
* You can climb a mountain

10:56.056 --> 10:59.359
* You can swim the sea

10:59.392 --> 11:03.030
* You can jump into the fire

11:03.063 --> 11:05.632
* But you'll never be free
Sorry, diarrhea.

11:05.665 --> 11:07.000
* You can shake me up

11:07.034 --> 11:09.036
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Aw, man!

11:09.069 --> 11:10.670
* Or I can break you down

11:10.704 --> 11:12.405
Can't kick this diarrhea.

11:12.439 --> 11:16.309
* Ohhh

11:16.343 --> 11:17.644
* Ohhh
[ School bell rings ]

11:17.677 --> 11:19.379
Dylan: Hey, Ray.

11:19.412 --> 11:22.049
Everyone's talking about
who's leaking party info.

11:22.082 --> 11:23.550
Oh.
They'll smoke out
that mole.

11:23.583 --> 11:25.318
I mean, at some point,
he'll get sloppy.

11:25.352 --> 11:26.519
Doubtful.

11:26.553 --> 11:28.856
Lot of talk
about this mole.

11:28.889 --> 11:30.590
Sure seems like he holds
all the cards.

11:30.623 --> 11:33.026
Maybe people shouldn't have
underestimated him.

11:35.095 --> 11:36.263
Let's go, Dad.

11:36.296 --> 11:38.231
Why are you always
eating fish?

11:38.265 --> 11:40.233
Hey, Anthony.
Huge party Friday, huh?

11:40.267 --> 11:42.035
Yeah. Why don't
you come along?

11:42.069 --> 11:44.604
Me?
Really?

11:44.637 --> 11:46.039
Yeah, why not?
You're a good kid.

11:46.073 --> 11:47.407
You think that?

11:47.440 --> 11:49.109
W-Why didn't you
say that before?

11:49.142 --> 11:50.110
Just don't tell anybody
about it.

11:50.143 --> 11:51.278
There's a mole out there.

11:51.311 --> 11:53.413
Unless...
you're the mole.

11:55.082 --> 11:56.216
[ Laughs ]
I'm just kidding.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.451
Oh. Ohh. [ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]

12:01.621 --> 12:03.623
Alright.
Yeah.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.530
Man: Good afternoon, shoppers.
Hungry for cheese?

12:10.563 --> 12:11.965
Visit Quincy by self-checkout
for a free sample.

12:16.103 --> 12:22.109
"Please use
regular chicken."

12:22.142 --> 12:24.077
Quincy to self-checkout,
please.

12:24.111 --> 12:25.078
Quincy to self-checkout.

12:29.249 --> 12:30.450
Oh, regular checkout.

12:30.483 --> 12:32.385
Thanks, Quincy.

12:32.419 --> 12:34.487
-Thanks, Quincy.
-You the man, Quincy.

12:34.521 --> 12:41.528
**

12:43.530 --> 12:45.332
Maya, Maya.
Uh, quick question.

12:45.365 --> 12:48.268
When I enter, it says I am
supposed to be running.

12:48.301 --> 12:50.503
Now, why am I doing that?

12:50.537 --> 12:53.106
The dog is chasing you.

12:53.140 --> 12:56.309
It's just running
from a dog.

12:56.343 --> 12:58.011
I mean, isn't that sort of
the obvious choice?

12:58.045 --> 12:59.847
You wrote this!

12:59.880 --> 13:01.481
Does not mean
I understand it.

13:01.514 --> 13:03.650
Alright, where's Joyce?
We have to start rehearsal.

13:03.683 --> 13:05.152
[ Quietly ] Um, she was --
Um, she -- she --

13:05.185 --> 13:06.619
I was promised stage fright.

13:06.653 --> 13:08.188
Are you scared
of the living room?

13:08.221 --> 13:10.290
She -- um, well, she --
Oh, she has car trouble?

13:10.323 --> 13:11.658
Okay, this isn't
gonna fall apart.

13:11.691 --> 13:12.993
I'm gonna go
and get Joyce.

13:13.026 --> 13:14.461
You all rehearse
the dog scene.

13:14.494 --> 13:15.929
We're hungry.

13:15.963 --> 13:17.597
Okay, who wants pizza bagels?

13:17.630 --> 13:18.498
Ooh!
Ooh, ooh, me!

13:18.531 --> 13:19.599
Oh, that you can say.

13:19.632 --> 13:23.336
**

13:23.370 --> 13:25.839
[ Alarm sounds ]

13:25.873 --> 13:31.845
**

13:31.879 --> 13:34.447
[ Machinery crunches, sputters ]

13:34.481 --> 13:36.183
[ Alarm beeping ]

13:36.216 --> 13:37.350
Uh, what happened?

13:37.384 --> 13:38.451
JJ, are you okay?

13:38.485 --> 13:39.853
What are you doing
back here?

13:39.887 --> 13:41.288
Oh, my God.

13:41.321 --> 13:42.489
Quincy.

13:42.522 --> 13:44.357
Murderer!
Settle down, Kevin.

13:44.391 --> 13:46.493
JJ, what's up?

13:46.526 --> 13:50.998
"You gave me a job
a cutout could do.

13:51.031 --> 13:53.200
Except he did it better.

13:53.233 --> 13:55.202
I quit."

13:55.235 --> 13:59.172
**

13:59.206 --> 14:00.173
Whatcha got, Ray?

14:00.207 --> 14:01.641
We hear there's
a big party coming up.

14:01.674 --> 14:03.043
You know anything?
You bet.

14:03.076 --> 14:06.379
The seniors are throwing
a huge blowout in spring.

14:06.413 --> 14:09.049
I'm talking a deejay,
dinner, black tie.

14:09.082 --> 14:11.551
You're talking
about prom.
Shh!

14:11.584 --> 14:13.553
Ray, help us out.

14:13.586 --> 14:15.188
I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

14:15.222 --> 14:16.189
Where's the party?

14:16.223 --> 14:17.690
I'm really torn.

14:19.092 --> 14:20.894
I'm in too deep.
I'm sorry. I want out.

14:20.928 --> 14:22.495
Oh, marone!
Jimmy, you hearing this?

14:22.529 --> 14:24.231
Honestly, no.
Allergic reaction.

14:24.264 --> 14:26.566
I think a shrimp found
its way into the calamari.

14:26.599 --> 14:28.401
I don't want to complain, but
can I get a fresh basket?

14:28.435 --> 14:31.071
You know, Ray,
we're the good guys.

14:31.104 --> 14:34.074
We're just parents
trying to protect our kids,

14:34.107 --> 14:36.043
trying to protect you.

14:36.076 --> 14:37.277
I mean,
it sure would be a shame

14:37.310 --> 14:40.914
if everyone at school found out
you were the mole.

14:40.948 --> 14:42.382
[ Shell cracks ]

14:42.415 --> 14:43.383
Yeah, I got to go
to the hospital.

14:43.416 --> 14:45.385
Can I get a rush
on the fresh basket?

14:45.418 --> 14:46.586
Maya:
Okay, everyone's here.

14:46.619 --> 14:47.955
We can start, finally.

14:48.621 --> 14:50.457
What?
-I am not acting

14:50.490 --> 14:54.061
until she apologizes
for wasting my time.

14:54.094 --> 14:56.029
Oh, I wouldn't call anything
you do acting.

14:56.063 --> 14:58.932
-[ Gasps ]
-Hey!

14:58.966 --> 15:00.033
Poke, poke, poke, poke,
poke, poke, poke, poke.
Stop touching each other.

15:00.067 --> 15:02.902
Separate! Let's go.
Places, everyone.

15:04.504 --> 15:07.040
[ Sighs ] Oh, Pepper.

15:07.074 --> 15:09.943
[ Bag rustles ]

15:09.977 --> 15:11.644
Oh, I'm back.

15:13.313 --> 15:16.916
I'm a mom, except for
a bunch of strangers

15:16.950 --> 15:18.485
I don't even care about.

15:18.518 --> 15:21.221
Hey, when you're done,

15:21.254 --> 15:24.291
I have some questions
about my character.

15:24.324 --> 15:25.425
[ Bag crumples ]

15:29.596 --> 15:32.065
Theater family, family-family,
we need to talk.

15:32.099 --> 15:34.101
I joined this play
to show you

15:34.134 --> 15:37.070
that there's more to me
than serving you,

15:37.104 --> 15:38.305
and now I'm just
serving you.

15:38.338 --> 15:40.873
It's okay. I've identified
who is to blame.

15:42.042 --> 15:43.010
Me.

15:43.043 --> 15:45.578
I pride myself
on being nurturing

15:45.612 --> 15:48.181
and getting things done,
but the thing is,

15:48.215 --> 15:51.351
if I do too much,
others take advantage of me.

15:51.384 --> 15:52.585
Well, that's about
to change.

15:52.619 --> 15:53.853
Please repeat after me.

15:53.886 --> 15:55.955
"Maya is not my servant."

15:55.989 --> 15:58.425
All: Maya is not my servant.

15:58.458 --> 15:59.993
"From this moment forward,

16:00.027 --> 16:02.829
she will do less,
and I will do more."

16:02.862 --> 16:04.631
All: From this moment forward,

16:04.664 --> 16:07.500
she will do less,
I will do more.

16:07.534 --> 16:08.868
You know, my hope is that

16:08.901 --> 16:10.303
my children will
see me differently.

16:10.337 --> 16:13.006
This may or may not happen,

16:13.040 --> 16:16.176
but what matters is that
I see me differently.

16:16.209 --> 16:17.310
"My hope is that
my children..."

16:17.344 --> 16:20.180
No, don't.
"...may see me differently.

16:20.213 --> 16:21.148
Goodbye."

16:21.181 --> 16:23.983
[ All gasp, murmur ]

16:24.017 --> 16:25.518
[ Applause ]

16:25.552 --> 16:28.155
I'm sorry, buddy.
I got you tangled up

16:28.188 --> 16:30.157
in this whole thing,
and for what?

16:30.190 --> 16:32.025
Some crab.

16:32.059 --> 16:34.361
I was being really...

16:34.394 --> 16:36.163
Oh, I really want
to say "shellfish."
[selfish]

16:36.196 --> 16:38.031
I just don't know
what to do.

16:38.065 --> 16:40.833
Now the teens love me,
but the parents own me.

16:40.867 --> 16:43.503
I mean, do I go to the party
or tell them to shut it down?

16:43.536 --> 16:46.873
I'm in so deep, and I'm so good
at playing both parts.

16:46.906 --> 16:48.575
This could go on forever.

16:48.608 --> 16:50.009
You're the mole?

16:51.411 --> 16:52.612
I suck at this.

16:54.214 --> 16:56.383
I'm sorry. I know you wanted
a real job,

16:56.416 --> 16:58.185
and I kind of let you down
on the "real" part.

16:58.218 --> 17:00.187
"It's okay.

17:00.220 --> 17:04.023
You were just
trying to help."

17:04.057 --> 17:05.225
Maybe this wasn't
the perfect fit,

17:05.258 --> 17:06.993
but we'll find
something else.

17:07.026 --> 17:09.396
Let me get your name tag
and vest.

17:09.429 --> 17:11.898
You know what?
Keep the vest.

17:11.931 --> 17:13.933
Fresco's gift to you.

17:16.069 --> 17:17.904
Sorry, I should
actually take the vest.

17:17.937 --> 17:19.272
We're always running out
of mediums.

17:20.273 --> 17:22.909
[ Door opens, closes ]

17:22.942 --> 17:28.948
**

17:28.981 --> 17:32.119
Look who's ready
for dress rehearsal.

17:32.152 --> 17:34.854
We made our own costumes,
we learned our lines,

17:34.887 --> 17:36.523
we even buried the hatchet.

17:36.556 --> 17:39.092
We did five trust falls.

17:39.126 --> 17:41.261
I caught him three times.

17:41.294 --> 17:42.829
[ Beeping ]

17:46.499 --> 17:48.901
JJ, how are you doing this?

17:48.935 --> 17:50.370
These things
break constantly,

17:50.403 --> 17:52.439
and there's, like,
500 error codes.

17:52.472 --> 17:55.875
"And I learned them all.

17:55.908 --> 17:58.077
I wanted to be useful,

17:58.111 --> 18:01.381
so I made myself useful."
Okay.

18:01.414 --> 18:05.385
How would you like to be our
self-checkout specialist?

18:05.418 --> 18:11.324
Welcome back, and here is
your first paycheck.

18:12.625 --> 18:14.294
You're damn right
it's for 12 cents.

18:14.327 --> 18:17.297
You broke the crusher,
and you killed Quincy, man.

18:17.330 --> 18:19.399
Get your ass back to work.

18:19.432 --> 18:25.505
**

18:25.538 --> 18:27.540
This play is about
Mr. Powers' life?

18:29.342 --> 18:30.643
With three intermissions?!

18:30.677 --> 18:32.145
Hey.

18:36.149 --> 18:38.418
What's up? Isn't it
almost time to start?

18:38.451 --> 18:39.419
The cast --
they're not coming.

18:39.452 --> 18:40.520
They've all got
food poisoning.

18:40.553 --> 18:41.921
Someone gave them
bad fish.

18:41.954 --> 18:43.089
That's crazy.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.324
How did they have room
for bad fish

18:44.357 --> 18:46.259
after all the good fish
I gav-- Oh.

18:46.293 --> 18:47.260
I mean, I guess
we just go home.

18:47.294 --> 18:48.461
No, you put too much
work into this,

18:48.495 --> 18:49.962
and you want the kids
to see you.

18:49.996 --> 18:51.631
Hang on.
Uh, hi. Excuse me.

18:51.664 --> 18:54.167
Some of the cast
has taken ill,

18:54.201 --> 18:55.435
but who still wants
to see a play?

18:55.468 --> 18:57.870
Everyone?
Yeah, no, we're doing this.

18:57.904 --> 18:59.606
Oh! I'm gonna break a leg.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.140
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:01.174 --> 19:04.677
I'm gonna ask you again, son,
for the last time.

19:04.711 --> 19:06.346
Do you want to live
with your mama

19:06.379 --> 19:08.348
or your daddy?

19:08.381 --> 19:09.549
I don't know.

19:09.582 --> 19:11.651
Where will my doggy,
Max, be?

19:11.684 --> 19:13.386
Tell the boy, Alice.

19:21.060 --> 19:22.195
[ Sobbing ]
You tell him, Richard.

19:22.229 --> 19:24.397
You're the one who did it.
[ Audience gasps ]

19:24.431 --> 19:27.234
Order! Order!

19:27.267 --> 19:30.203
I will not have my courtroom
turned into a circus!

19:30.237 --> 19:34.374
Is it me, or is she seriously
good as the judge?

19:34.407 --> 19:36.042
[ Piano plays ]
Shh!

19:36.075 --> 19:38.911
* I'm just a boy
from Maryland *

19:38.945 --> 19:42.515
* What am I doin' here
in Pennsylvania? *

19:42.549 --> 19:44.050
They're so close.

19:44.083 --> 19:45.518
What do you mean,
you're leaving?

19:45.552 --> 19:48.221
You're my world,
my everything

19:48.255 --> 19:51.057
[ Sniffles ]
[ Whispering ] You don't
even like Mr. Powers.

19:51.090 --> 19:52.492
He gave you a "D"
last year.

19:52.525 --> 19:54.927
I didn't know
what he gave up for me.

19:54.961 --> 19:59.366
* How do I know it's Heaven?

19:59.399 --> 20:01.434
**

20:01.468 --> 20:02.902
Max!

20:02.935 --> 20:04.337
[ Audience "aww"s ]

20:04.371 --> 20:06.706
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:08.575 --> 20:09.676
Mom, that was amazing.

20:09.709 --> 20:11.077
Really?

20:11.110 --> 20:13.613
"You transported me,
and not in a van."

20:13.646 --> 20:15.448
[ Laughs ]

20:17.417 --> 20:19.085
[ Dance music plays,
indistinct talking ]

20:19.118 --> 20:21.388
Hey, man. Where you been?
Sorry, I was at my mom's play.

20:21.421 --> 20:22.555
That's awesome, bro.

20:22.589 --> 20:23.923
What a great son.

20:25.157 --> 20:27.560
Now I have to betray
my best friend?

20:27.594 --> 20:28.961
[ Cellphone dings ]

20:31.464 --> 20:33.433
[ Groans ] Stupid parents
always signing texts.

20:33.466 --> 20:35.468
[ Cellphone chimes ]
I got the address.

20:35.502 --> 20:38.371
Let's go keep
our children pure.

20:38.405 --> 20:40.573
Now, who wants to drive?
I'm smashed.

20:40.607 --> 20:42.208
* Hey, she gon' shake it,
she gon' shake it *

20:42.241 --> 20:43.610
* She gon' drop that *
Aha!

20:43.643 --> 20:44.977
* We gon' keep on making paper,
we won't stop that *

20:46.145 --> 20:47.880
Party's over, parents.

20:47.914 --> 20:50.249
What is this?
Where's my hot daughter?

20:50.283 --> 20:51.618
Your father's gonna hear
about this.

20:51.651 --> 20:53.586
Oh, he already knows.

20:53.620 --> 20:55.388
This ends now.

20:55.422 --> 20:57.490
Some bad fish poisoned
the whole cast

20:57.524 --> 21:00.960
of a pretty weird play.

21:00.993 --> 21:03.463
Be a shame if people were to
find out who the purveyor was.

21:03.496 --> 21:05.131
Be a real shame.

21:05.164 --> 21:08.000
How dare you use poor Ray
as your pawn?

21:08.034 --> 21:10.603
If you want to know where
your kids are, ask them.

21:10.637 --> 21:13.973
They want to talk.
They just want you to listen.

21:14.006 --> 21:15.575
[ Sighs ]
Alright, let's go.

21:15.608 --> 21:17.477
Wise words, honey.
Let's go home.

21:17.510 --> 21:19.178
[ Door closes ]

21:19.211 --> 21:20.647
Hey, forgot to ask.
Whose house is this?

21:20.680 --> 21:23.616
Oh, my God.
You and your questions!
